      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elmsford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village grew around the New York and Putnam Railroad station, which opened in the 1870s and served passengers until 1958.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2,
        23
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elmsford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The historic Elmsford train station on Saw Mill River Road now houses a local restaurant, preserving its original façade.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elmsford%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Carol Nichols Park, dedicated in 1996, offers softball, basketball, tennis courts, a kiddie park, and a sprinkler park for kids.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
